(firstQuint)Ultrasound Paravertebral Block in Breast Surgery.

.

 General anaesthesia is currently the conventional technique used for breast surgery.

 Thoracic Paravertebral block (PVB) has been used with multiple injection.

 We compared a single injection thoracic PVB with general anaesthesia (GA) in 20 consenting patients, scheduled for unilateral breast surgery.

